{"timestamp": "2026-05-22 12:16:57,583", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-22T12:16:57.583400\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Build match-3 detection and clearing logic: scan the grid for gem matches, remove matched gems, apply gravity for falling gems, handle chain reactions, and add match-3 bonus scoring.\", \"result\": \"```python\\nfrom collections import defaultdict\\n\\ndef detect_matches(grid):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Detects horizontal and vertical matches of 3 or more gems in the grid.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    matches = []\\n    height = len(grid)\\n    width = len(grid[0]) if height > 0 else 0\\n\\n    # Horizontal matches\\n    for row in range(height):\\n        for col in range(width - 2):\\n            if grid[row][col] and grid[row][col] == grid[row][col+1] == grid[row][col+2]:\\n                match = [(row, col), (row, col+1), (row, col+2)]\\n            ...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"failed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The current `detect_matches` flattens all matched cells into one list, losing the grouping of individual runs and preventing per-run scoring.\\n2. `handle_chain_reactions` treats its `initial_matches` as a flat list of cells, so `len(initial_matches)` no longer corresponds to run lengths.\\n3. Gravity logic may stop early if there are multiple gaps in a column.\\n4. We need to score each run by its length, then apply a single chain bonus per reaction step.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\n# match3_logic.py\\n\\n# Scoring parameters\\nMATCH_CLEAR_SCORES    = {3:  50, 4: 100, 5: 200}\\nEXTRA_PER_GEM         =  20   # points per gem beyond length 5\\nCHAIN_BONUS_MULTIPLIER = 1.5\\n\\ndef create_empty_grid(rows, cols):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Return a rows×cols grid initialized to None.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    return [[None for _ in range(cols)] for _ in range(rows)]\\n\\ndef detect_matches(grid):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Find all non-overlapping horizontal and vertical runs of length>=3.\\n    Returns a list of matches, each match is a list of (r, c) tuples.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    matches = []\\n    rows = len(grid)\\n    cols = len(grid[0]) if rows else 0\\n\\n    # Horizontal\\n    for r in range(rows):\\n        c = 0\\n        while c < cols - 2:\\n            color = grid[r][c]\\n            if color is None:\\n                c += 1\\n                continue\\n            length = 1\\n            while c + length < cols and grid[r][c + length] == color:\\n                length += 1\\n            if length >= 3:\\n                matches.append([(r, c + i) for i in range(length)])\\n                c += length\\n            else:\\n                c += 1\\n\\n    # Vertical\\n    for c in range(cols):\\n        r = 0\\n        while r < rows - 2:\\n            color = grid[r][c]\\n            if color is None:\\n                r += 1\\n                continue\\n            length = 1\\n            while r + length < rows and grid[r + length][c] == color:\\n                length += 1\\n            if length >= 3:\\n                matches.append([(r + i, c) for i in range(length)])\\n                r += length\\n            else:\\n                r += 1\\n\\n    return matches\\n\\ndef clear_matches(grid, matches):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Clears all matched cells (sets them to None).\\n    Returns the total number of gems cleared.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    cleared = 0\\n    for match in matches:\\n        for r, c in match:\\n            if grid[r][c] is not None:\\n                grid[r][c] = None\\n                cleared += 1\\n    return cleared\\n\\ndef apply_gravity(grid):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Collapse each column so that non-None values fall to the bottom.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    rows = len(grid)\\n    cols = len(grid[0]) if rows else 0\\n    for c in range(cols):\\n        write_r = rows - 1\\n        for r in range(rows - 1, -1, -1):\\n            if grid[r][c] is not None:\\n                grid[write_r][c] = grid[r][c]\\n                if write_r != r:\\n                    grid[r][c] = None\\n                write_r -= 1\\n        # fill above with None\\n        for r in range(write_r, -1, -1):\\n            grid[r][c] = None\\n\\ndef handle_chain_reaction_and_score(grid):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Repeatedly detect, clear, and apply gravity until no more matches.\\n    Scores each run by length, sums them per step, then applies a single\\n    chain bonus for each successive reaction.\\n    Returns (total_score, total_cleared, chain_length).\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    total_score   = 0\\n    total_cleared = 0\\n    chain_length  = 0\\n\\n    while True:\\n        matches = detect_matches(grid)\\n        if not matches:\\n            break\\n\\n        # score all runs this step\\n        step_score = 0\\n        for match in matches:\\n            length = len(match)\\n            if length in MATCH_CLEAR_SCORES:\\n                step_score += MATCH_CLEAR_SCORES[length]\\n            else:\\n                # extra points for runs > 5\\n                base = MATCH_CLEAR_SCORES.get(5, 0)\\n                step_score += base + (length - 5) * EXTRA_PER_GEM\\n\\n        # apply chain bonus (first clear no bonus, second clear ×1.5, third ×1.5², …)\\n        if chain_length > 0:\\n            step_score = int(step_score * (CHAIN_BONUS_MULTIPLIER ** chain_length))\\n\\n        # clear and drop\\n        cleared = clear_matches(grid, matches)\\n        apply_gravity(grid)\\n\\n        total_score   += step_score\\n        total_cleared += cleared\\n        chain_length  += 1\\n\\n    return total_score, total_cleared, chain_length\\n\\n# Example Usage\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Define a simple grid (None or color IDs)\\n    grid = create_empty_grid(6, 6)\\n    # Horizontal match of 4 at row 0\\n    grid[0][0:4] = [1, 1, 1, 1]\\n    # Vertical match of 3 at col 3\\n    grid[1][3] = grid[2][3] = grid[3][3] = 2\\n\\n    print(\\\"Before:\\\")\\n    for row in grid:\\n        print(row)\\n\\n    score, cleared, chains = handle_chain_reaction_and_score(grid)\\n\\n    print(f\\\"\\\\nAfter: score={score}, cleared={cleared}, chains={chains}\\\")\\n    for row in grid:\\n        print(row)\\n```\"}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-22 12:17:09,052", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nDevelop a game that fuses Tetris and Bejeweled mechanics. \\nThis game needs to add keyboard control function.\\nFalling tetrominoes should lock into a grid and transform into colored gems. \\nThe game must support both Tetris line-clearing and Bejeweled match-3 clearing, triggering chain reactions and bonus points. \\nInclude a GUI (using a framework like Pygame) that displays the game grid, current score, and next tetromino preview, along with smooth animations. \\nNo sound effects are needed.\\n\\nOutput Format: python\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task0:\\n  Objective: Define core data structures and constants: grid representation, tetromino shapes, gem colors, and scoring parameters.\\n  Result: from enum import Enum\\nfrom collections import namedtuple\\n\\n# Grid dimensions\\nGRID_WIDTH = 10\\nGRID_HEIGHT = 20\\n\\n# Point on the grid\\nPoint = namedtuple('Point', ['x', 'y'])\\n\\n# Tetromino types\\nclass PieceType(Enum):\\n    I = 'I'\\n    O = 'O'\\n    T = 'T'\\n    S = 'S'\\n    Z = 'Z'\\n    J = 'J'\\n    L = 'L'\\n\\n# Tetromino shapes: list of rotations, each rotation is list of 4 Points\\nTETROMINO_SHAPES = {\\n    PieceType.I: [\\n        [Point(0,1), Point(1,1), Point(2,1), Point(3,1)],\\n        [Point(2,0), Point(2,1), Point(2,2), Point(2,3)],\\n        [Point(0,2), Point(1,2), Point(2,2), Point(3,2)],\\n        [Point(1,0), Point(1,1), Point(1,2), Point(1,3)],\\n    ],\\n    PieceType.O: [\\n        [Point(1,0), Point(2,0), Point(1,1), Point(2,1)],\\n    ] * 4,\\n    PieceType.T: [\\n        [Point(1,0), Point(0,1), Point(1,1), Point(2,1)],\\n        [Point(1,0), Point(1,1), Point(2,1), Point(1,2)],\\n        [Point(0,1), Point(1,1), Point(2,1), Point(1,2)],\\n        [Point(1,0), Point(0,1), Point(1,1), Point(1,2)],\\n    ],\\n    PieceType.S: [\\n        [Point(1,0), Point(2,0), Point(0,1), Point(1,1)],\\n        [Point(1,0), Point(1,1), Point(2,1), Point(2,2)],\\n        [Point(1,1), Point(2,1), Point(0,2), Point(1,2)],\\n        [Point(0,0), Point(0,1), Point(1,1), Point(1,2)],\\n    ],\\n    PieceType.Z: [\\n        [Point(0,0), Point(1,0), Point(1,1), Point(2,1)],\\n        [Point(2,0), Point(1,1), Point(2,1), Point(1,2)],\\n        [Point(0,1), Point(1,1), Point(1,2), Point(2,2)],\\n        [Point(1,0), Point(0,1), Point(1,1), Point(0,2)],\\n    ],\\n    PieceType.J: [\\n        [Point(0,0), Point(0,1), Point(1,1), Point(2,1)],\\n        [Point(1,0), Point(2,0), Point(1,1), Point(1,2)],\\n        [Point(0,1), Point(1,1), Point(2,1), Point(2,2)],\\n        [Point(1,0), Point(1,1), Point(0,2), Point(1,2)],\\n    ],\\n    PieceType.L: [\\n        [Point(2,0), Point(0,1), Point(1,1), Point(2,1)],\\n        [Point(1,0), Point(1,1), Point(1,2), Point(2,2)],\\n        [Point(0,1), Point(1,1), Point(2,1), Point(0,2)],\\n        [Point(0,0), Point(1,0), Point(1,1), Point(1,2)],\\n    ],\\n}\\n\\n# Color palette (RGB) for tetrominoes and gems\\nTETROMINO_COLORS = {\\n    PieceType.I: (0, 240, 240),\\n    PieceType.O: (240, 240,   0),\\n    PieceType.T: (160,   0, 240),\\n    PieceType.S: (0, 240,   0),\\n    PieceType.Z: (240,   0,   0),\\n    PieceType.J: (0,   0, 240),\\n    PieceType.L: (240, 160,   0),\\n}\\n\\nGEM_COLORS = list(TETROMINO_COLORS.values())\\n\\n# Scoring parameters\\nLINE_CLEAR_SCORES = {\\n    1: 100,\\n    2: 300,\\n    3: 500,\\n    4: 800,\\n}\\n\\nMATCH_CLEAR_SCORES = {\\n    3: 50,\\n    4: 100,\\n    5: 200,\\n}\\n\\nCHAIN_BONUS_MULTIPLIER = 1.5\\n\\n# Grid cell representation: None or (r, g, b)\\ndef create_empty_grid():\\n    return [[None for _ in range(GRID_WIDTH)] for _ in range(GRID_HEIGHT)]\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task4:\\n  Objective: Develop the Pygame-based GUI and main game loop: render the grid, animations, current score, next tetromino preview, and integrate controls with mechanics modules.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nBuild match-3 detection and clearing logic: scan the grid for gem matches, remove matched gems, apply gravity for falling gems, handle chain reactions, and add match-3 bonus scoring.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nimport pygame\\nimport random\\nfrom collections import namedtuple\\nfrom enum import Enum\\n\\n# Assuming GRID_WIDTH, GRID_HEIGHT, Point, PieceType, TETROMINO_SHAPES, TETROMINO_COLORS, GEM_COLORS, LINE_CLEAR_SCORES, MATCH_CLEAR_SCORES, CHAIN_BONUS_MULTIPLIER, create_empty_grid are defined in task0\\n\\nclass GameState(Enum):\\n    PLAYING = 0\\n    GAME_OVER = 1\\n\\nclass TetrisBejeweled:\\n    def __init__(self, grid_width, grid_height):\\n        self.grid_width = grid_width\\n        self.grid_height = grid_height\\n        self.grid = create_empty_grid()\\n        self.score = 0\\n        self.game_state = GameState.PLAYING\\n        self.chain_reaction = False\\n        self.chain_multiplier = 1.0\\n\\n    def detect_matches(self):\\n        matches = []\\n        # Horizontal matches\\n        for y in range(self.grid_height):\\n            for x in range(self.grid_width - 2):\\n                if self.grid[y][x] and self.grid[y][x] == self.grid[y][x+1] == self.grid[y][x+2]:\\n                    match_len = 3\\n                    while x + match_len < self.grid_width and self.grid[y][x] == self.grid[y][x+match_len]:\\n                        match_len += 1\\n                    matches.append([(x + i, y) for i in range(match_len)])\\n\\n        # Vertical matches\\n        for x in range(self.grid_width):\\n            for y in range(self.grid_height - 2):\\n                if self.grid[y][x] and self.grid[y][x] == self.grid[y+1][x] == self.grid[y+2][x]:\\n                    match_len = 3\\n                    while y + match_len < self.grid_height and self.grid[y][x] == self.grid[y+match_len][x]:\\n                        match_len += 1\\n                    matches.append([(x, y + i) for i in range(match_len)])\\n        \\n        # Remove duplicate matches (matches sharing same gem)\\n        unique_matches = []\\n        for match in matches:\\n            if not any(coord in sum(unique_matches, []) for coord in match):\\n                unique_matches.append(match)\\n        return unique_matches\\n\\n    def clear_matches(self, matches):\\n        cleared_count = 0\\n        for match in matches:\\n            cleared_count += len(match)\\n            for x, y in match:\\n                self.grid[y][x] = None  # Clear the gem\\n        return cleared_count\\n\\n    def apply_gravity(self):\\n        for x in range(self.grid_width):\\n            empty_pos = None\\n            for y in range(self.grid_height):\\n                if self.grid[y][x] is None and empty_pos is None:\\n                    empty_pos = y\\n                elif self.grid[y][x] and empty_pos is not None:\\n                    self.grid[empty_pos][x] = self.grid[y][x]\\n                    self.grid[y][x] = None\\n                    \\n                    # find next empty pos\\n                    new_empty_pos = empty_pos + 1\\n                    while new_empty_pos < self.grid_height and self.grid[new_empty_pos][x] is not None:\\n                        new_empty_pos += 1\\n                    \\n                    if new_empty_pos < self.grid_height and self.grid[new_empty_pos][x] is None:\\n                        empty_pos = new_empty_pos\\n                    else:\\n                         empty_pos = None\\n\\n\\n    def handle_chain_reactions(self):\\n        total_score = 0\\n        chain_active = True\\n        while chain_active:\\n            matches = self.detect_matches()\\n            if matches:\\n                cleared_count = self.clear_matches(matches)\\n                self.apply_gravity()\\n                match_score = MATCH_CLEAR_SCORES.get(len(matches[0]), 200)  # Base score for a match\\n                chain_score = int(match_score * self.chain_multiplier)\\n                total_score += chain_score\\n                self.score += chain_score\\n                self.chain_multiplier *= CHAIN_BONUS_MULTIPLIER  # Increase multiplier for next chain\\n                \\n                #print(f\\\"Chain reaction! Score: {chain_score}, Multiplier: {self.chain_multiplier}\\\") #debug\\n            else:\\n                chain_active = False  # No more matches, chain ends\\n                self.chain_multiplier = 1.0  # Reset multiplier for the next piece\\n                \\n        return total_score # accumulated score\\n\\n    def process_grid(self):\\n        matches = self.detect_matches()\\n        if matches:\\n            self.chain_reaction = True\\n            cleared_count = self.clear_matches(matches)\\n            self.apply_gravity()\\n            score_increase = self.handle_chain_reactions()  # includes match score\\n            #self.score += score_increase\\n        else:\\n            self.chain_reaction = False\\n\\n    def lock_piece(self, piece, x, y, rotation_index):\\n        for point in TETROMINO_SHAPES[piece.piece_type][rotation_index]:\\n            grid_x = x + point.x\\n            grid_y = y + point.y\\n            if 0 <= grid_x < self.grid_width and 0 <= grid_y < self.grid_height:\\n                self.grid[grid_y][grid_x] = piece.color  # Gem color from piece\\n        \\n        self.process_grid()  # Check and clear matches after locking the piece\\n    \\n    def clear_lines(self):\\n        lines_to_clear = []\\n        for y in range(self.grid_height):\\n            if all(self.grid[y][x] is not None for x in range(self.grid_width)):\\n                lines_to_clear.append(y)\\n\\n        if lines_to_clear:\\n            for y in lines_to_clear:\\n                del self.grid[y]\\n                self.grid.insert(0, [None] * self.grid_width)  # Add empty line at the top\\n            num_lines_cleared = len(lines_to_clear)\\n            self.score += LINE_CLEAR_SCORES.get(num_lines_cleared, 800) # score from line clearing\\n\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-22T12:17:09.051916\"\n}"}
